Monte Carlo Simulation

This chart overlays multiple equity curves, each from a random shuffling of the historical trades, to visualize the range of possible outcomes.

Monte Carlo Equity Bands

This chart extends the historical equity curve by simulating 100 future trades. The process is repeated 1,000 times to generate 5th and 95th percentile bands, showing the expected performance range.

Projected P&L Confidence Intervals

The 90% confidence interval for the expected Profit & Loss after a specific number of future trades, based on 1,000 simulations.
